@node FUTURE "Mystic Meg?  No, a little more accurate than that... :)"

@{fg shine}Future developments@{fg text}

 Hopefully, I'll continue to improve Connexion, and perhaps make it into
something a little moe special than it is at the moment.  If you have any
ideas for improving this game, please @{" drop me a line " Link FINAL}.

 Current ideas include, in no particular order...

 @{fg shine}o@{fg text} Sound FX - when (and if) I find some decent ones :)

 @{fg shine}o@{fg text} Serial link option (not very likely, but it would be cool :)

 @{fg shine}o@{fg text} Token designer, allowing the user to make their own tokens to use when
   playing.  One possibility would be including an IFF of a grid with the
   game, which the user could modify in a paint package (and animate the
   token like an animbrush to see what it would look like).  The IFF,
   once modified, could be sent back to Anarchy Software via Email, and
   the new token might be included in the next release, with due credit
   to the author, of course.

 @{fg shine}o@{fg text} Background music?  Well, I thought of this one, but decided
   against it, because @{b}a)@{ub} I just cannot write any MODs successfully (this
   has nothing to do with lack of musical ability though, which annoys me)
   and @{b}b)@{ub} I always listen to the radio, or put a CD on when playing,
   which sounds a lot better than most in-game music.  There's a greater
   possibility of liking the music as well, and it's a lot more versatile.

@endnode
